      Warren Buffett
   =20
 =20
What,  boring:A New York City dinner between=C2=A0Warren Buffett=C2=A0and A=
lleghany Corp. Chief Executive Officer=C2=A0Joseph Brandon=C2=A0kicked off =
one of Berkshire Hathaway Inc.=E2=80=99s latest deal hunts.The pair met for=
 dinner on March 7, when Buffett made it clear that Berkshire was intereste=
d in buying Alleghany for $850 a share, according to a=C2=A0regulatory fili=
ng=C2=A0released Monday. That conversation would jump-start Berkshire=E2=80=
=99s=C2=A0bid=C2=A0for Alleghany that culminated in a $11.6 billion deal fo=
r the insurer announced later that month. =E2=80=A6At that dinner, Buffett =
insisted that the price wouldn=E2=80=99t include fees for financial adviser=
s. That quirk resulted in an odd $848.02 announced deal price. The fee for =
Goldman Sachs Group Inc., which is advising Alleghany, would come out of th=
e proceeds for insurer=E2=80=99s shareholders.What a non-Buffett way to neg=
otiate a merger. He met the CEO for dinner? And the CEO used to work for hi=
m? Meh. When Warren Buffett invested $5 billion in=C2=A0Bank of America Cor=
p. after the financial crisis, he didn=E2=80=99t just call up CEO Brian Moy=
nihan, whose phone number Buffett absolutely absolutely absolutely absolute=
ly absolutely absolutely had. Instead, he  allegedly called up Bank of Amer=
ica=E2=80=99s public switchboard and asked to be transferred to the CEO, be=
cause executing a deal efficiently is far less important to Buffett than ha=
ving a good folksy anecdote is.I would have assumed that if Buffett wanted =
to buy Alleghany the move would be to wander into a McDonald=E2=80=99s in A=
lleghany County, North Carolina, where Alleghany=E2=80=99s headquarters=C2=
=A0is not located, order a Cherry Coke,=C2=A0and say =E2=80=9Chey does=C2=
=A0anyone here know anyone at Alleghany Corp.?=E2=80=9D And then sort of fo=
llow leads from there until he washed up a few months later at the desk of =
a receptionist at Alleghany=E2=80=99s=C2=A0actual headquarters in New York.=
 =E2=80=9CHello I have $11.6 billion here, I would like to buy your company=
,=E2=80=9D he could say, and then hand over like a million suitcases full o=
f crumpled one-dollar bills to the baffled receptionist. =E2=80=9CRemember,=
 no bankers=E2=80=99 fees!=E2=80=9D That would make a good =E2=80=9CBackgro=
und of the Merger=E2=80=9D in the proxy statement.
