om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Newswire insider trading</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The main way to insider trade is to kn=
ow big news about public companies before the news is public. If you work a=
t a public company, you will occasionally learn big news about your company=
 before it is public, and then you can trade on it, but (1) there will not =
be that many opportunities and (2) you will probably get caught and get in =
trouble. If you want to insider trade a <em>lot</em>, the better place to b=
e is at some intermediary that regularly gets big news about=C2=A0<em>many=
=C2=A0</em>public companies just before it becomes public. So investment ba=
nkers and mergers-and-acquisitions lawyers are classic insider traders: The=
y learn big news (mergers) about many different companies (their clients) b=
efore the news is public. Still you will only have so many clients, and als=
o you=E2=80=99ll get caught.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For really amb=
itious insider trading, the ideal intermediary is one of the companies that=
 takes big news from lots of companies, holds on to it briefly, and then ma=
kes it public. We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
27343269.270594/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzI=
wMjEtMTItMjEvdGhlcmUtcy1pbnNpZGUtaW5mb3JtYXRpb24taW4tc2VjLWZpbGluZ3M_Y21waW=
Q9QkJEMDQxMjIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZ=
XR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwNDEyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cBaf687c2f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> talked a few months ago</a> about Edgarizers=
, the=C2=A0companies that =E2=80=9Cprovide proprietary, cloud-based softwar=
e platforms to facilitate public companies=E2=80=99 filing of periodic and =
other reports with the SEC.=E2=80=9D A company has some news, it puts the n=
ews in a Securities and Exchange Commission filing, it sends the filing to =
a service provider to file with the SEC. Sometimes it sends the filing to t=
he service provider=C2=A0<em>early:=C2=A0</em>It maintains a draft on the p=
rovider=E2=80=99s system, it finalizes the draft on that system over hours =
or days, and=C2=A0<em>then=C2=A0</em>it hits the filing button. If you hack=
 into the service provider, as a Russian military intelligence officer alle=
gedly did, then you can get lots of SEC filings early and trade on them and=
 make money.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the real prizes are the ne=
wswires, the companies that transmit press releases for companies. Any time=
 a company has big news it is going to put out a press release, and sometim=
es companies will upload their press releases to the newswires hours or day=
s before they are final. If you hack into the newswires, as some <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27343269.270594/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cudGhldmVyZ2UuY29tLzIwMTgvOC8yMi8xNzcxNjYyMi9zZWMtYnVzaW5lc3Mtd2lyZS1oYWN=
rLXN0b2xlbi1wcmVzcy1yZWxlYXNlLWZyYXVkLXVrcmFpbmU/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4=
dbecd45" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;">Ukrainian hackers</a>=C2=A0did <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27343269.270594/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnL=
mNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTUtMDgtMTEvd2h5LW5vdC1pbnNpZGVyLXRyYWRlLW9u=
